{"by":"cleverdash","id":47757697,"parent":47753689,"text":"The trend of CLI-first design because AI agents need it is interesting. We ended up in the same place building developer tools, the CLI and API came first because that&#x27;s what agents actually consume. The dashboard came after.<p>The cf permissions check idea from the top comment is great. One thing I&#x27;ve found is that agents are surprisingly good at using CLIs but terrible at diagnosing why a command failed. Clear error messages with the exact fix (&quot;missing scope X, run cf token add --scope X&quot;) matter way more for agent usability than the happy path.","time":1776113731,"type":"comment"}